{
  "question_text": "<h3>Maximum Sum of 3 Non-Overlapping Subarrays</h3><p>Find indices of three non-overlapping subarrays of length $k$ with maximum sum.</p>",
  "difficulty": "HARD",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "nums, k.",
  "output_format": "[i1, i2, i3].",
  "constraints": [
    "n <= 2*10^4"
  ],
  "explanation": "Compute sums of all possible subarrays of length $k$. Use DP to track maximum sums and their indices for 1, 2, and 3 subarrays.",
  "answer": "def maxSumOfThreeSubarrays(nums, k):\n    n = len(nums); w = [sum(nums[:k])]\n    for i in range(1, n-k+1): w.append(w[-1] - nums[i-1] + nums[i+k-1])\n    l = [0] * len(w); cur = 0\n    for i in range(len(w)): \n        if w[i] > w[cur]: cur = i\n        l[i] = cur\n    r = [0] * len(w); cur = len(w)-1\n    for i in range(len(w)-1, -1, -1):\n        if w[i] >= w[cur]: cur = i\n        r[i] = cur\n    res = [-1,-1,-1]; mx = 0\n    for i in range(k, len(w)-k):\n        cur_mx = w[l[i-k]] + w[i] + w[r[i+k]]\n        if cur_mx > mx: mx = cur_mx; res = [l[i-k], i, r[i+k]]\n    return res",
